Gerry,<br><br>
Thanks for your very kind words.<br><br>
I sometimes agonize over what I post on these pages. My feelings on The Wall are no exception. Once I get over the hump and post, I never regret it. It is a part of the &quot;process&quot; within me that really makes it all worthwhile.<br><br>
I recently read out-loud some of my written words about The Wall with a friend. I knew then that they were really part of me. Though the pain slowly diminishes with each step on this path, my bond with it all grows tighter. I don't know what is next, but I am not afraid. I do know that the pain will never fully leave, but that's OK. The pain will always linger to be sure I never loose touch with it all. I guess that is what I am really all about.<br><br>
Gerry, thanks again for you comments.<br><br>
Art<br>

